editorialNotes.standard: Shooting movies on film may be a dying art, but just because we live in the digital age doesn’t mean we have to abandon our analogue past. We get warm, nostalgic fuzzies from 8mm Vintage Camera’s grainy, flickery film filters and lens effects, conjuring up memories of vacation travelogues screened in wood-panelled basements. It’s not just about old-school kicks, though—this powerful suite of tools can give any video an authentic period look.
editorialNotes.short: The easy way to create authentic vintage movies.
